So we can avoid the same comments over and over, check the description for all the links! Also, yes, ChrisFish is me, and not an impostor. snippet.textDisplay: In NewZealand the polish and rubbing compound products you used start from $45-$80 per/item and application pads $23-$30 👎 my paint is as badly oxidised as this SUV was at the start of the video, had to opt for a cheaper option (TurtleWax) -heavy duty rubbing compound + polixsh + wax, ran me upwards of $90 and 2 hours of elbow grease for ABSOLUTELY NO IMPROVEMENT 😔  for low prices alone I wish I lived in your country lol we don’t have eBay & Amazon here and global shipping from either website is expensive and takes 3 months to arrive. Unlucky.... will try Meguiars products another time....?

snippet.textDisplay: Fantastic video. I own all of the products here and had attempted to restore my 2010 Ford that has lived its life in the harsh Australian sun its entire life, so the roof and doors on one side where completely chalky and no longer reflective. When i first attempted i did not have much luck, though the rest of the car looked great! After seeing this video i noticed that i was not using enough product, nor was i rubbing for long enough. Gave it another attempt today with this in mind and the doors have turned from chalk to a perfect mirror using the same products (except different wax) as seen here.
